![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/1578168101090-1MZZ7FPN9YRI54B6O5F4/image-asset.jpeg)

It's the SPOOKIEST time of the year, and to celebrate the guys at CBC are doing a deep dive into one of the most frightening protagonists in comic book history, Spawn. Not only is this episode filled with facts about his origin, power set and weaknesses, but we even find time to do a full review on the 1997 film of the same name! Starring Michael Jai White, Martin Sheen and John Leguizamo, its been quite some time since most of us has seen this film! Did it hold up? Is Spawn a likeable hero? Does anyone like that clown? Find out on this episode of Major Issues!

If you can, please leave us a **_review_** on [**ITunes**](https://podcasts.apple.com/us/podcast/major-issues-podcast/id1321720972) so we can grow our audience and grow as podcasters! Rate us where ever podcasts are found. Don't forget to check out our merchandise! All episodes of Major Issues are brought to you by **ComicBook Clique**, the one stop for the latest and greatest things to come to comic books and comic book media.  
  
